Ecopetrol Says Pipeline Repaired After Mudslides Near Bogota

-- B y   A n d r e a   J a r a m i l l o
-- 
2011-04-29T13:08:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-29/ecopetrol-says-pipeline-repaired-after-mudslides-near-bogota.html
Ecopetrol SA (ECOPETL) ,  Colombia ’s largest
oil company, said it fixed an oil pipeline damaged by mudslides
in Guaduas, north of Bogota.  Ecopetrol has begun pumping fuel through the pipeline and
it should reach the capital by the weekend, a spokesman who
asked not to be named according to company policy said in a
telephone interview today. Colombia’s aviation agency said in a
statement yesterday Bogota’s international airport was facing
jet fuel shortages because of the damage in the pipeline.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andrea Jaramillo at 
 ajaramillo1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dale Crofts at 
